description: Number of pairs of twin primes whose smaller element is <= 10^n-th prime.
links: Index entries for sequences related to numbers of primes in various ranges
example: a(1)=5 since the 10th prime is 29 and the first 5 twin primes are {3,5}, {5,7}, {11,13}, {17,19} and {29,31}.
author: Dennis S. Kluk (mathemagician(AT)ameritech.net)
extensions: More terms from _Labos Elemer_, Oct 13 2000; _Jud McCranie_, Dec 30 2000
